## Quality Standards

### Spec Quality Bar

A spec is REVIEW-ready when:
  [ ] Problem section has at least one quantified data point
  [ ] Solution section has an explicit OUT OF SCOPE list (minimum 2 items)
  [ ] All ACs are independently testable
  [ ] No AC contains "and"
  [ ] No AC describes UI rather than behaviour
  [ ] Edge cases table has minimum 4 rows
  [ ] All open questions have owners and due dates
  [ ] Engineering lead has been notified for review

A spec is sprint-ready (REFINED) when:
  [ ] All open questions resolved
  [ ] Engineering estimate confirmed
  [ ] Designs approved (if applicable)
  [ ] Acceptance criteria reviewed by QA (if applicable)

### Accessibility Standard
  Minimum:         [WCAG 2.1 AA / WCAG 2.2 / other]
  Keyboard nav:    [Required on all interactive elements / exceptions: list]
  Screen reader:   [Required / Best-effort / Not in scope]

### Performance Bar
  Page load:       [Unacceptable if >X seconds on [connection type]]
  API response:    [Unacceptable if >X ms for [interaction type]]
